The paper focuses on using deep learning for recognizing scanned receipts, which involves computer vision (text detection) and natural language processing (text recognition). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information extraction, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the text recognition module uses attention-based encoder-decoder, which is a popular technique in natural language processing and falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves pre-processing and OCR verification, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
